25 (A) THE DEPARTMENT SHALL ESTABLISH MEMORANDUMS OF
26 UNDERSTANDING WITH FEDERAL AND STATE AGENCIES TO FACILITATE
27 DATA–SHARING IN ORDER TO CONDUCT:
28 (1) MONTHLY DEATH RECORD REVIEWS, USING THE VITAL
29 STATISTICS ADMINISTRATION DATABASE TO IDENTIFY DECEASED INDIVIDUALS
30 WHO ARE PROGRAM RECIPIENTS;
31 (2) QUARTERLY REVIEWS, IN CONSULTATION WITH THE MARYLAND
32 DEPARTMENT OF LABOR, TO DETERMINE THE EFFECT OF EMPLOYMENT OR WAGE
33 CHANGES ON THE CONTINUING ELIGIBILITY OF PROGRAM RECIPIENTS;

