1 (A) (1) IN THIS SECTION THE FOLLOWING WORDS HAVE THE MEANINGS
2 INDICATED.
3 (2) “EXPANSION POPULATION” MEANS INDIVIDUALS WHO ARE
4 ELIGIBLE TO PARTICIPATE IN THE PROGRAM UNDER § 1902(A)(10)(A)(I)(VIII) OF
5 THE FEDERAL SOCIAL SECURITY ACT, COMMONLY KNOWN AS THE MEDICAID
6 EXPANSION POPULATION UNDER THE AFFORDABLE CARE ACT.
7 (3) “NONEXPANSION POPULATION” MEANS ALL INDIVIDUALS
8 ELIGIBLE TO PARTICIPATE IN THE PROGRAM WHO DO NOT QUALIFY UNDER THE
9 EXPANSION POPULATION, INCLUDING PREGNANT WOMEN, CHILDREN, ELDERLY
10 INDIVIDUALS, AND INDIVIDUALS WITH DISABILITIES.
11 (4) “RETROACTIVE ELIGIBILITY” MEANS PROGRAM COVERAGE FOR
12 SERVICES PROVIDED BEFORE THE MONTH OF APPLICATION AS AUTHORIZED BY 42
13 U.S.C. § 1396(A)(34).
14 (B) (1) THE DEPARTMENT SHALL LIMIT RETROACTIVE ELIGIBILITY FOR
15 INITIAL PROGRAM APPLICANTS TO:
16 (I) FOR INDIVIDUALS DETERMINED TO BE ELIGIBLE AS PART
17 OF THE EXPANSION POPULATION, 1 MONTH BEFORE THE MONTH IN WHICH THE
18 INDIVIDUAL SUBMITS AN APPLICATION; AND
19 (II) FOR INDIVIDUALS ELIGIBLE AS PART OF THE
20 NONEXPANSION POPULATION, 2 MONTHS BEFORE THE MONTH IN WHICH THE
21 INDIVIDUAL SUBMITS AN APPLICATION.
22 (2) THE LIMITATIONS ESTABLISHED UNDER PARAGRAPH (1) OF THIS
23 SUBSECTION:
24 (I) APPLY ONLY TO INITIAL APPLICATIONS TO THE PROGRAM;
25 AND
26 (II) MAY NOT BE CONSTRUED TO AFFECT ELIGIBILITY FOR
27 CONTINUOUS OR ONGOING COVERAGE.
28 (C) THE DEPARTMENT SHALL:
29 (1) ESTABLISH PROCEDURES TO NOTIFY APPLICANTS AND
30 PROVIDERS OF CHANGES IN THE RETROACTIVE ELIGIBILITY POLICY; AND

