25 (A) (1) IN THIS SECTION THE FOLLOWING WORDS HAVE THE MEANINGS
26 INDICATED.
27 (2) “APPLICABLE PROGRAM RECIPIENT” MEANS AN INDIVIDUAL WHO
28 IS SUBJECT TO WORK REQUIREMENTS UNDER FEDERAL LAW, REGULATION, OR
29 GUIDANCE.
30 (3) “WORK REQUIREMENTS” MEANS THE REQUIREMENTS
31 ESTABLISHED UNDER 42 U.S.C. § 1396A(XX).

HOUSE BILL 1331 9
1 (B) (1) ON OR BEFORE DECEMBER 31, 2026, THE DEPARTMENT SHALL
2 IMPLEMENT WORK REQUIREMENTS FOR ALL APPLICABLE PROGRAM RECIPIENTS.
3 (2) THE DEPARTMENT SHALL REQUIRE DOCUMENTARY EVIDENCE OF
4 COMPLIANCE WITH THIS SECTION.
5 (C) THE DEPARTMENT MAY NOT APPROVE AN EXEMPTION FROM THE
6 REQUIREMENTS OF THIS SECTION FOR AN INDIVIDUAL, BASED ON THE STATUS OF
7 THE INDIVIDUAL AS MEDICALLY FRAIL OR OTHERWISE BEING AN INDIVIDUAL WITH
8 SPECIAL MEDICAL NEEDS, UNLESS THE INDIVIDUAL HAS BEEN CERTIFIED AS
9 HAVING A DISABLING MENTAL DISORDER, A PHYSICAL, INTELLECTUAL, OR
10 DEVELOPMENTAL DISABILITY THAT SIGNIFICANTLY IMPAIRS THE INDIVIDUAL’S
11 ABILITY TO PERFORM ACTIVITIES OF DAILY LIVING, OR IS IN TREATMENT FOR A
12 CHRONIC SUBSTANCE USE DISORDER, BY:
13 (1) A PHYSICIAN;
14 (2) A PHYSICIAN’S ASSISTANT;
15 (3) A NURSE;
16 (4) A NURSE PRACTITIONER;
17 (5) A REPRESENTATIVE OF A PHYSICIAN’S OFFICE AUTHORIZED TO
18 PROVIDE THE CERTIFICATION;
19 (6) A PSYCHOLOGIST; OR
20 (7) A SOCIAL WORKER.
21 (D) THE DEPARTMENT MAY NOT:
22 (1) EXPAND THE DESCRIPTION OF AN INDIVIDUAL WHO IS MEDICALLY
23 FRAIL OR OTHERWISE AN INDIVIDUAL WITH SPECIAL MEDICAL NEEDS BEYOND THE
24 SCOPE ESTABLISHED UNDER 42 C.F.R. § 440.315(F);
25 (2) SEEK OR IMPLEMENT AN ADDITIONAL EXEMPTION TO WORK
26 REQUIREMENTS UNLESS SPECIFICALLY AUTHORIZED UNDER THIS TITLE; OR
27 (3) AUTHORIZE A MANAGED CARE ORGANIZATION TO DETERMINE
28 WHETHER A PROGRAM RECIPIENT IS EXEMPT FROM THE REQUIREMENTS OF THIS
29 SECTION.

