11 15–123.4.
12 (A) IN THIS SECTION, “QUALIFIED CITIZEN” MEANS AN INDIVIDUAL WHO IS
13 A RESIDENT OF THE UNITED STATES AND WHO IS:
14 (1) A CITIZEN OR IS OTHERWISE A NATIONAL OF THE UNITED STATES;
15 (2) AN ALIEN LAWFULLY ADMITTED FOR PERMANENT RESIDENCE AS
16 AN IMMIGRANT;
17 (3) AN ALIEN WHO HAS BEEN GRANTED THE STATUS OF CUBAN OR
18 HAITIAN ENTRANT, AS DEFINED IN SECTION 501(E) OF THE REFUGEE EDUCATION
19 ASSISTANCE ACT OF 1980; OR
20 (4) AN INDIVIDUAL LAWFULLY RESIDING IN THE UNITED STATES IN
21 ACCORDANCE WITH A COMPACT OF FREE ASSOCIATION, AS APPLICABLE UNDER 8
22 U.S.C. § 1612(B)(2)(G).
23 (B) (1) THE DEPARTMENT MAY NOT PROVIDE COVERAGE UNDER THE
24 PROGRAM TO AN INDIVIDUAL UNLESS THE INDIVIDUAL IS A QUALIFIED CITIZEN.
25 (2) THE DEPARTMENT SHALL REQUIRE THAT INCOME OF INELIGIBLE
26 HOUSEHOLD MEMBERS BE INCLUDED WHEN CALCULATING FINANCIAL ELIGIBILITY
27 FOR THE PROGRAM.
28 (C) THE DEPARTMENT SHALL INCLUDE AN IMMIGRATION STATUS FIELD ON
29 ALL APPLICATIONS FOR PROGRAM SERVICES.

