10 SUPPLEMENTAL NUTRITION ASSISTANCE PROGRAM FRAUD, INCLUDING:
11 (I) THE NUMBER OF HOUSEHOLDS INVESTIGATED;
12 (II) THE NUMBER OF INDIVIDUALS REFERRED FOR
13 PROSECUTION;
14 (III) THE TOTAL NUMBER AND AMOUNT OF IMPROPER PAYMENTS
15 RECOVERED;
16 (IV) THE PERCENTAGE OF INELIGIBLE RECIPIENTS IDENTIFIED;
17 AND
18 (V) THE TOTAL EXPENDITURE OF FUNDS ON OUT–OF–STATE
19 ELECTRONIC BENEFITS TRANSFER CARD TRANSACTIONS.
20 (10) THE DEPARTMENT SHALL ADOPT REGULATIONS TO CARRY OUT
21 THIS SECTION.
22 5–503.
23 Subject to the State budget, the Department shall provide food supplement benefits
24 to a legal immigrant who:
25 (1) is a minor;
26 (2) is ineligible for federally funded Supplemental Nutrition Assistance
27 Program benefits because of immigration status;
28 (3) meets all other Supplemental Nutrition Assistance Program eligibility
29 requirements; and
30 (4) meets any other requirements of the State.

16 HOUSE BILL 1331
1 5–503.1.
2 (A) AN INDIVIDUAL MAY NOT RECEIVE BENEFITS UNDER THE
3 SUPPLEMENTAL NUTRITION ASSISTANCE PROGRAM UNLESS THE INDIVIDUAL IS A
4 RESIDENT OF THE UNITED STATES AND IS:
5 (1) A CITIZEN OR NATIONAL OF THE UNITED STATES;
6 (2) AN ALIEN LAWFULLY ADMITTED FOR PERMANENT RESIDENCE AS
7 AN IMMIGRANT;
8 (3) AN ALIEN WHO HAS BEEN GRANTED THE STATUS OF CUBAN OR
9 HAITIAN ENTRANT, AS DEFINED IN SECTION 501(E) OF THE REFUGEE EDUCATION
10 ASSISTANCE ACT OF 1980; OR
11 (4) AN INDIVIDUAL LAWFULLY RESIDING IN THE UNITED STATES IN
12 ACCORDANCE WITH A COMPACT OF FREE ASSOCIATION, AS APPLICABLE UNDER 8
13 U.S.C. § 1612(B)(2)(G).
14 (B) (1) THE DEPARTMENT SHALL VERIFY THAT AN INDIVIDUAL IS
15 ELIGIBLE TO RECEIVE BENEFITS UNDER THE SUPPLEMENTAL NUTRITION
16 ASSISTANCE PROGRAM UNDER 7 U.S.C. § 2015(F) AND SUBSECTION (A) OF THIS
17 SECTION BY REQUIRING AN INDIVIDUAL TO PROVIDE PROOF OF CITIZENSHIP OR
18 ELIGIBLE ALIEN STATUS BY PROVIDING DOCUMENTATION, INCLUDING:
19 (I) A BIRTH OR HOSPITAL RECORD;
20 (II) A VOTER REGISTRATION CARD;
21 (III) A U.S. PASSPORT; AND
22 (IV) U.S. CUSTOMS AND IMMIGRATION SERVICE
23 DOCUMENTATION.
24 (2) (I) IF AN INDIVIDUAL IS ELIGIBLE TO RECEIVE BENEFITS
25 UNDER THE SUPPLEMENTAL NUTRITION ASSISTANCE PROGRAM UNDER
26 SUBSECTION (A) OF THIS SECTION AND IS NOT A CITIZEN OR NATIONAL OF THE
27 UNITED STATES, THE DEPARTMENT SHALL VERIFY THE INDIVIDUAL’S STATUS
28 USING THE SYSTEMATIC ALIEN VERIFICATION FOR ENTITLEMENTS ONLINE
29 SERVICE.

HOUSE BILL 1331 17
1 (II) ON A MONTHLY BASIS, THE DEPARTMENT SHALL ASSESS
2 THE CONTINUED ELIGIBILITY OF AN INDIVIDUAL WHO IS NOT A CITIZEN OR
3 NATIONAL OF THE UNITED STATES USING THE SYSTEMATIC ALIEN VERIFICATION
4 FOR ENTITLEMENTS ONLINE SERVICE OR ANY OTHER FEDERAL DATABASE USED TO
5 DETERMINE CITIZENSHIP OR IMMIGRATION STATUS.
6 (C) THE DEPARTMENT SHALL SUBMIT TO THE U.S. DEPARTMENT OF
7 AGRICULTURE INFORMATION CONCERNING ANY INDIVIDUAL FOR WHOM THE
8 DEPARTMENT IS UNABLE TO VERIFY ELIGIBLE IMMIGRATION STATUS UNDER
9 SUBSECTION (A) OF THIS SECTION, REGARDLESS OF WHETHER THE INDIVIDUAL IS
10 APPLYING FOR BENEFITS UNDER THE SUPPLEMENTAL NUTRITION ASSISTANCE
11 PROGRAM.
12 (D) (1) WHEN DETERMINING THE ELIGIBILITY AND BENEFIT AMOUNT
13 FOR ANY HOUSEHOLD APPLYING FOR BENEFITS UNDER THE SUPPLEMENTAL
14 NUTRITION ASSISTANCE PROGRAM, THE DEPARTMENT SHALL INCLUDE THE
15 INCOME AND FINANCIAL RESOURCES OF ANY INDIVIDUAL IN THE HOUSEHOLD WHO
16 IS INELIGIBLE TO RECEIVE BENEFITS UNDER THE SUPPLEMENTAL NUTRITION
17 ASSISTANCE PROGRAM UNDER 7 U.S.C. § 2015(F) AND SUBSECTION (A) OF THIS
18 SECTION.
19 (2) NOTWITHSTANDING ANY OPTIONS PROVIDED UNDER 7 C.F.R. §
20 273.11(C)(3), THE DEPARTMENT MAY NOT PRORATE OR EXCLUDE THE INCOME OR
21 FINANCIAL RESOURCES OF INELIGIBLE INDIVIDUALS.
22 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That, if any provision of this Act or
23 the application of any provision of this Act to any person or circumstance is held invalid for
24 any reason in a court of competent jurisdiction, the invalidity does not affect other
25 provisions or any other application of this Act that can be given effect without the invalid
26 provision or application, and for this purpose the provisions of this Act are declared
27 severable.
28 SECTION 3. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect July
29 1, 2026.

